I wouldn&#39;t recommend using DomainScope even where it&#39;s available -- it&#39;s 
less flexible and efficient than other options, and eliminated from 
later releases.

Also, the OnDomainsDecideRule suggested here doesn&#39;t really add anything 
over the default SurtPrefixedDecideRule -- it just provides a shortcut 
for trimming all provided seeds/SURT-prefixes to their &#39;domain&#39; portion. 
That&#39;s also easy to do with SurtPrefixedDecideRule, and sticking closer 
to the recommended default starting scope is usually the best approach.

(That also goes for its relative position in the rules list: since the 
last rule to assert a decision &#39;wins&#39;, if you want the TooManyHops and 
NotSurePrefixed rules to have the desired limiting effect, you&#39;ll want 
your main &#39;accepting&#39; rule to come before them.)

- Gordon @ IA

On 12/8/10 11:23 PM, Mohamed Elsayed wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; It is simple. If you use Heritrix 1, then you can go to modules after
&gt; creating the job and change the scope to DomainScope instead of
&gt; DecidingScope. If you use Heritrix 3, then you can modify
&gt; crawler-beans.cxml. We just need to modify &quot;scope&quot; as following:
&gt;
&gt; &lt;bean id=&quot;scope&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.DecideRuleSequence&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;    &lt;property name=&quot;rules&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;list&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- Begin by REJECTing all... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.RejectDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...but REJECT those more than a configured link-hop-count from start... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TooManyHopsDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;        &lt;property name=&quot;maxHops&quot; value=&quot;5&quot; /&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...but ACCEPT those more than a configured link-hop-count from start... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TransclusionDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxTransHops&quot; value=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxSpeculativeHops&quot; value=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...but REJECT those from a configurable (initially empty) set of REJECT SURTs... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.NotSurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;            &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt;            &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt;            &lt;property name=&quot;surtsDumpFile&quot; value=&quot;negative-surts.dump&quot; /&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;surtsSourceFile&quot; value=&quot;&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...then ACCEPT any URI that is in one of the domains of the configured set. --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.OnDomainsDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;        &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;ACCEPT&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those from a configurable (initially empty) set of URI regexes... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.MatchesListRegexDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;            &lt;property name=&quot;decision&quot; value=&quot;REJECT&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;listLogicalOr&quot; value=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;regexList&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;             &lt;list&gt;
&gt;
&gt;             &lt;/list&gt;
&gt;
&gt;            &lt;/property&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those with suspicious repeating path-segments... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PathologicalPathDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;       &lt;!--&lt;property name=&quot;maxRepetitions&quot; value=&quot;2&quot; /&gt;  --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...and REJECT those with more than threshold number of path-segments... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.TooManyPathSegmentsDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;        &lt;property name=&quot;maxPathDepth&quot; value=&quot;20&quot; /&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...but always ACCEPT those marked as prerequisitee for another URI... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.PrerequisiteAcceptDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;!-- ...but always REJECT those with unsupported URI schemes --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.SchemeNotInSetDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/list&gt;
&gt;
&gt;    &lt;/property&gt;
&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
